article.headline: Virginia 91, Elon 61
article.story: CHARLOTTESVILLE, Va. (AP) -- Sean Singletary led Virginia with 20 points and Adrian Joseph scored all 16 of his points in the second half as the Cavaliers ran away from Elon on Saturday 91-61. Singletary, who made three of four three pointers, scored in double figures for the 33rd straight game for Virginia (9-2). He also had eight assists. The Cavaliers started off slow, trailing the Phoenix (5-7) 7-6 four minutes into the game. Singletary hit a jumper at the 15:02 mark to put Virginia ahead for good, and added a three-pointer for good measure 22 seconds later to put the Cavs up 11-7. The Cavaliers widened their lead to 36-18 at 5:45 in the first half, but the Phoenix were able to close to within 47-34 by intermission behind a jumper by Monty Sanders, who led Elon with 15. In the second half, the Phoenix pulled within 49-39 at the 18:49 mark behind a three-pointer by Montell Wilson. Joseph answered with his only three-pointer at 17:14, and had 10 points in the opening 3:40 of the half. Virginia extended its lead to 59-39 at 15:01 when Singletary hit two free throws. Brett James and Ola Atoyebi each finished with 13 points. Elon had 20 turnovers in the game.
